  "system": {
    "description": "<p>A shield composed of high impact plastic, complete with inlaid electrical contacts, that when the shield is activated, will shock and incapacitate the person struck. A stun shield provides one-quarter cover in one direction. A stun shield has to be activated, which costs 2 Combat Points. On a successful hit with an activated shield, the stun shield deals 1d3 points of Electricity damage (do not add the character&rsquo;s POW bonus) and the target must make a Fortitude Saving Throw [TN13] or be paralyzed for 1d2 rounds. Stun shields can not be disarmed.</p>",
